📖 Overview
## 📸 Project Overview


<p align="center">
  <img src="assets/overview.png" width="900">assets/overview.png <img/>
</p>


GO-RELOADED is a command-line text processor written in Go.
It reads an input file, applies transformation rules and formatting logic, then writes the processed output into a new file.

This project demonstrates:

Advanced string manipulation

Regular expression parsing

Token processing

Slice mutation logic

CLI file handling

Unit testing in Go

Clean modular architecture

✨ Features
🔤 Text Case Modifiers
Modifier	Description	Example
(up)	Uppercase previous word	hello (up) → HELLO
(low)	Lowercase previous word	HELLO (low) → hello
(cap)	Capitalize previous word	hello (cap) → Hello
(cap, N)	Capitalize previous N words	(cap, 6)
🔢 Numeric Conversions
Modifier	Description
(hex)	Converts previous hexadecimal number to decimal
(bin)	Converts previous binary number to decimal

Example:

Simply add 42 (hex) and 10 (bin)

Output:

Simply add 66 and 2
🧠 Grammar & Formatting Engine

✔ Article correction (a → an)
✔ Proper punctuation spacing
✔ Ellipsis handling (...)
✔ Quote normalization (' text ' → 'text')
✔ Smart tokenization preserving modifiers

📂 Project Architecture
go-reloaded/
│
├── go.mod
├── main.go
├── processor.go
├── utils.go
└── processor_test.go
🔹 main.go

Handles CLI arguments and file I/O.

🔹 processor.go

Core transformation engine.

🔹 utils.go

Helper utilities (token removal, capitalization, vowel detection).

🔹 processor_test.go

Unit tests validating all functionality.

▶️ Usage
Run the program
go run . input.txt output.txt
Run tests
go test

Expected output:

PASS
ok      github.com/GO-RELOADED
